    <text type="letter">
        <body>
            <pb xml:id="leaf001r" facs="loc.01875.005_large.jpg" type="recto"/>
            <note type="editorial" place="top" resp="#ww">Ans June 30. '76</note>
            <note type="editorial" place="top" resp="#ww"><hi rend="underline">John
                Rogers</hi></note>
            <opener>
                <address>
                    <addrLine>New Britain</addrLine>
                </address>
                <dateline>
                    <date when="1876-03-28">March 28 1876</date>
                </dateline>
                <salute>Dear Friend</salute>
            </opener>
            <p>It is some time <choice>
                <sic>cince</sic>
                <corr>since</corr>
            </choice> I heard from you, why do you not write I should like to <choice>
                    <sic>here</sic>
                    <corr>hear</corr>
                </choice> from you very much This leaves me well thank God but I have been sick
                most all winter my wife<ptr target="n5001"/> is sick at <choice>
                    <sic>presant</sic>
                    <corr>present</corr>
                </choice> But the Lord has been good to me in past and I know if I put my trust in
                him I shall come <choice>
                    <sic>of</sic>
                    <corr>off</corr>
                </choice> more than conker <pb xml:id="leaf001v" facs="loc.01875.006_large.jpg"
                    type="verso"/> I feel that Christ is very <choice>
                    <sic>prescious</sic>
                    <corr>precious</corr>
                </choice> to me I feel that peace and <choice>
                    <sic>contentiment</sic>
                    <corr>contentment</corr>
                </choice> of mind that I never had before</p>
            <p>I have <choice>
                <sic>learnd</sic>
                <corr>learned</corr>
                </choice> to trust him for all things both spiritual and <choice>
                    <sic>temperal</sic>
                    <corr>temporal</corr>
                </choice> and I can truly say that he never leaves nor forsakes those <choice>
                    <sic>tha</sic>
                    <corr>that</corr>
                </choice> put trust in him and I know that he is able to save to the uttermost all
                that will come to him and he gives us joy and peace in this life and the life to
                come O that all might <choice>
                    <sic>fell</sic>
                    <corr>feel</corr>
                </choice> the love of Jesus in their souls We have had several here this past winter
                and about six Hundred have <pb xml:id="leaf002r" facs="loc.01875.007_large.jpg"
                    type="recto"/> given their hearts to the Saviour and still there is more to
                follow.</p>
            <p>I <choice>
                    <sic>supose</sic>
                    <corr>suppose</corr>
                </choice> they are making great <choice>
                    <sic>prepreration</sic>
                    <corr>preparation</corr>
                </choice> for the <choice>
                    <sic>exabishtion</sic>
                    <corr>exhibition</corr>
                </choice> in Philadelphia I should like to come on there this summer very much to
                spend a few days and I shall if I can <hi rend="underline">we all send love</hi></p>
            <p>write soon</p>
            <closer>
                <salute>I remain yours</salute>
                <signed>John M Rogers</signed>
                <address>
                    <addrLine>New Britain</addrLine>
                    <addrLine>Conn</addrLine>
                </address>
            </closer>
            <postscript>
                <p>write soon</p>
            </postscript>
            <pb xml:id="leaf002v" facs="loc.01875.008_large.jpg" type="verso"/>
        </body>
